ars/xebra-sedan |date=2010-01-03}}</ref>\n|$10,000 or \u20ac7,500\n|data-sort-value=\"25\"|{{convert|25|mi|km|abbr=in|order=flip|round=5}}\n|\n|\n|-align=center\n\n![[Tesla Roadster (2008)|Tesla Roadster]]<ref>650 scheduled for delivery in 2008, first one delivered 1 February 2008</ref><ref>[http://www.megawattmotorworks.com/display.asp?dismode=article&artid=293 Tesla Roadster \u2018Signature One Hundred\u2019 Series Sells Out] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160411200354/http://www.megawattmotorworks.com/display.asp?dismode=article&artid=293 |date=11 April 2016 }}</ref><ref>[http://news.zdnet.com/2100-9595_22-6167658.html Tesla to open five dealer outlets] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080316220043/http://news.zdnet.com/2100-9595_22-6167658.html |date=16 March 2008 }}</ref>\n|2008\u20132012\n| 2,500\n|130&nbsp;mph<br /> 210&nbsp;km/h <ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070715004824/http://www.teslamotors.com/performance/specs.php]</ref>\n|US$109,000 or \u20ac99,000 base price <ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070715004824/http://www.teslamotors.com/performance/specs.php]</ref>\n|data-sort-value=\"220\"|{{convert|220|mi|km|abbr=in|order=flip|round=5}}\n|less than 2 cents/mile off peak recharge\n|\n|-align=center\n\n! colspan=\"8\"|Modern series production electric cars\n\n|-align=center\n![[Mitsubishi i MiEV]]<br />(Peugeot iOn/Citro\u00ebn C-Zero)\n|2009\u2013\n| ~37,600<br />{{as of|2016|06|lc=y}}<ref name=Top10Global062016>{{cite news|url=http://www.hybridcars.com/global-10-best-selling-plug-in-cars-are-accelerating-forward/ | title=Global 10 Best-Selling Plug-In Cars Are Accelerating Forward | first=Jeff | last=Cobb| work=HybridCars.com| date=2016-08-10| accessdate=2016-08-14}} ''{{As of|2016|06}}, cumulative global sales of the top selling plug-in electric cars were led by the Nissan Leaf (over 228,000), followed by the Tesla Model S (129,393),  BYD Qin (56,191), Renault Zoe (51,193), BMW i3 (around 49,500), Mitsubishi i-MiEV f