inion.com/2017/07/19/lista-completa-de-nominados-a-premios-tu-mundo-2017/|website=laopinion.com|accessdate=19 July 2017|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=\"laopinionwinners\">{{cite web|title=Lista de todos los ganadores de Premios Tu Mundo 2017|url=https://laopinion.com/2017/08/24/lista-de-todos-los-ganadores-de-premios-tu-mundo-2017/|website=laopinion.com|accessdate=25 August 2017|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n| [[Your World Awards for Novela of the Year|Favorite S\u00faper Series]]\n| ''Se\u00f1ora Acero''\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"laopinion.com\" /><ref name=\"laopinionwinners\" />\n|-\n| [[Your World Awards for Favorite Lead Actor|Favorite Lead Actor]]\n| [[Luis Ernesto Franco]]\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"laopinion.com\" /><ref name=\"laopinionwinners\" />\n|-\n| [[Your World Awards for Favorite Lead Actress|Favorite Lead Actress]]\n| [[Carolina Miranda (actress)|Carolina Miranda]]\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"laopinion.com\" /><ref name=\"laopinionwinners\" />\n|-\n| The Best Bad Boy\n| [[Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Torre]]\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"laopinion.com\" /><ref name=\"laopinionwinners\" />\n|-\n| The Best Bad Girl\n| [[Gaby Espino]]\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"laopinion.com\" /><ref name=\"laopinionwinners\" />\n|-\n| Favorite Actor\n| [[Michel Duval]]\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"laopinion.com\" /><ref name=\"laopinionwinners\" />\n|-\n| The Perfect Couple\n| Luis Ernesto Franco and Carolina Miranda\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"laopinion.com\" /><ref name=\"laopinionwinners\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=2| Soy Sexy And I Know It\n| [[Ana Luc\u00eda Dom\u00ednguez]]\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"laopinion.com\" /><ref name=\"laopinionwinners\" />\n|-\n| Michel Duval\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"laopinion.com\" /><ref name=\"laopinionwinners\" />\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb title|3904068}}\n{{Se\u00f1ora Acero}}\n{{Telemundo telenovelas and series}}\n{{Argos Comunicaci\u00f3n's telenovelas}}\n{{Telemundo programming}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Senora Acero}}\n[[Category:2014 telenovelas]]\n[[Category:Se\u00f1ora Acero]]\n[[Category:2015 telenovelas]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language telenovelas]]\n[[Category:Telemundo telenovelas]]\n[[Category:2014 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2014 Mexican television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2016 telenovelas]]\n[[Category:Argos Comunicaci\u00f3n telenovelas]]\n[[Category:2017 telenovelas]]\n[[Category:2010s American LGBT-related television series]]\n[[Category:2018 telenovelas]]\n[[Category:Films about drugs]]\n[[Category:Films about Mexican drug cartels]]\n[[Category:2019 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:2019 Mexican television series endings]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Se\u00f1ora Acero\n| image                = Se\u00f1ora Acero title card.jpg\n| image_size           = \n| caption              = ''Se\u00f1ora Acero'' season four title card \n| genre                = [[Telenovela]]\n| creator              = Roberto Stopello\n| writer               = {{Plainlist|{{collapsible list|title={{nobold|Various}}|bullets=on|\n* Juan Manuel Andrade\n* Gabriela Caballero\n* Camilo Hern\u00e1ndez\n* Christian Jim\u00e9nez\n* Jos\u00e9 Vicente Spataro\t\n* Sergio Mendoza\n* Jos\u00e9 Miguel N\u00fa\u00f1ez\n* Amar\u00eds P\u00e1ez\n* Indira P\u00e1ez\n}}\n}}\n| director             = {{Plainlist|{{collapsible list|title={{nobold|Various}}|bullets=on|\n* [[Miguel Varoni]] <small>(2014\u20132019)</small>\n* Walter Doehner\n* Jaime Segura\n* Carlos Villegas Rosales\n* Daniel Aguirre\n* Danny Gavidia\n* Marcela Mej\u00eda\t\n* Camilo Villamizar\n* Felipe Aguilar D.\n}}\n}}\n| creative_director    = {{Plainlist|\n* Olin D\u00edaz\n* Maria Eugenia Gonz\u00e1lez-Naranjo\n* Claudia Vergara\n}}\n| starring             = {{Plainlist|<!-- Organized by broadcast credit order, with new main cast added to the end of the list -->\n* [[Blanca Soto]]\n* [[Litzy]]\n* [[Dami\u00e1n Alc\u00e1zar]]\n* [[Marco P\u00e9rez (actor)|Marco P\u00e9rez]]\n* [[Jorge Z\u00e1rate (actor)|Jorge Z\u00e1rate]]\n* [[Rossana San Juan]]\n* [[Andr\u00e9s Palacios]]\n* [[Rebecca Jones]]\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Res\u00e9ndez]]\n* [[Lincoln Palomeque]]\n* [[Alejandro Calva]]\n* [[Carolina Miranda (actress)|Carolina Miranda]]\n* [[Luis Ernesto Franco]]\n* [[Sergio Goyri]]\n* [[Laura Flores]]\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Torre]]\n* [[Ana Luc\u00eda Dom\u00ednguez]]\n* [[Gaby Espino]]\n* [[Diego Cadavid]]\n* [[William Miller (actor, born 1978)|William Miller]]\n* [[David Chocarro]]\n* [[Paulina Gait\u00e1n]] \n* [[Mauricio Islas]]\n* [[Dagoberto Gama]]\n* [[Maria Rojo]] \n}}\n| theme_music_composer = Mario Quintero Lara\n| opentheme            = [[#Music|See below]]\n| country              = United States\n| language             = Spanish\n| num_seasons          = 5<!-- Or num_series. Increment when new seasons/series begin. See template documentation for more info. -->\n| num_episodes         = 387<!-- Value is incremented when new episodes air. See template documentation for more info. -->\n| list_episodes        = List of Se\u00f1ora Acero episodes\n| executive_producer   = {{Plainlist|\n* Mariana Iskandariani <small>(2015\u20132019)</small>\n* [[Carmen Cecilia Urbaneja]]\n* Ana Graciela Ugalde\t\n* [[Joshua Mintz]] <small>(2014\u20132016)</small>\n* Martha Godoy\n}}\n| location             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Miami Florida]]\n* [[Cuernavaca, Morelos]]\n* [[Pachuca, Hidalgo]]\n* [[Tijuana, Baja California]]\n* [[Guadalajara Jalisco]]\n* [[Mexico City, Mexico]]\n* [[Los Angeles California]]\n* [[El Paso, Texas]] <small>(season 3\u20135)</small>\n* [[San Diego, California]]\n* [[Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez, Chihuahua]]\n* [[Buenos Aires, Argentina]]\n}}\n| cinematography       = {{Plainlist|\n* Pablo Reyes\n* Dami\u00e1n Aguilar\n* Esteban de Llaca\n* Andr\u00e9s Le\u00f3n Becker\n* Juan Bernardo S\u00e1nchez Mej\u00eda\n* Juan Pablo Ambris\n* Mariano Diluch\n}}\n| editor               = {{Plainlist|\n* Ramiro Pardo\n* Marcos Gonz\u00e1lez\n* Rigel Sosa Andrade\n* Francisco Nogueras\n* Horacio Valle\n* Cheryl Sanchez\n* Carlos Leal\n}}\n| camera               = [[Multi-camera]]\n| runtime              = <!-- Reliable source required -->\n| company              = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Argos Comunicaci\u00f3n]]\n* [[Telemundo Global Studios]]\n}}\n| distributor          = [[Telemundo Internacional]]\n| network              = [[Telemundo]]\n| picture_format       = [[HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| audio_format         = [[Stereophonic sound]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2014|9|23|df=yes}} \n| last_aired           = {{End date|2019|1|29|df=yes}} \n| related              = <!-- To be used only for remakes, spin-offs, and adaptations -->\n| website              = http://www.telemundo.com/super-series/senora-acero\n}}\n\n'''''Se\u00f1ora Acero''''', also known as '''''Se\u00f1ora Acero: La Coyote''''', is an American [[telenovela]] created by Roberto Stopello and it started airing on American broadcast channel [[Telemundo]] on 23 September 2014, and concluded on 29 January 2019. Produced by [[Argos Comunicaci\u00f3n]] and [[Telemundo Studios]], and distributed by [[Telemundo Internacional]].\n\nSet and filmed in [[Mexico]], Seasons 1 and 2 tell the story of Sara Aguilar ([[Blanca Soto]]), a young female housewife, who by self-indecision ends up becoming the most powerful [[drug trafficker]] in all of [[Mexico]] to be able to protect her son and her friends.<ref>{{cite web|title=\"Se\u00f1ora Acero\", la madre que se hizo mafiosa por su hijo|url=http://www.lacapital.com.ar/escenario/senora-acero-la-madre-que-se-hizo-mafiosa-su-hijo-n473918.html|website=lacapital.com.ar|accessdate=9 September 2017|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=G\u00f3mez|first1=Marlon|title=Conociendo a la Se\u00f1ora Acero|url=http://elmundonewspaper.com/news/2014/sep/18/conociendo-la-senora-acero/|website=elmundonewspaper.com|accessdate=9 September 2017|language=Spanish}}</ref> Seasons 3 and 4 focus on the life of Vicenta Rigores better known as \"La Coyote\" ([[Carolina Miranda (actress)|Carolina Miranda]]),<ref>{{cite web|title=Vicenta Rigores|url=http://www.telemundo.com/super-series/2016/07/18/senora-acero-vicenta-rigores-carolina-miranda|website=telemundo.com|accessdate=9 September 2017|language=Spanish}}</ref> a beautiful young woman who helps immigrants cross the borders of Mexico to go to the [[United States]], after learning that she is the daughter of Vicente Acero and has the blood of Acero, ends up joining the world of drug traffickers along with her brother Salvador Acero ([[Michel Duval]]) so she can continue to help immigrants and defend against injustices.<ref>{{cite web|title=Carolina Miranda ser\u00e1 la nueva \"Se\u00f1ora Acero, La Coyote\"|url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/elsentinel/os-es-senora-acero-coyote-telemundo-20160713-story.html|website=orlandosentinel.com|accessdate=9 September 2017|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 February 2018, [[Telemundo]] confirmed that the show has been renewed for a fifth season.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gonz\u00e1lez|first1=Mois\u00e9s|title=Se\u00f1ora Acero tendr\u00e1 una quinta temporada: \"Apuntamos hacia una historia nueva, un reto distinto\", nos avanza su creador|url=http://peopleenespanol.com/telenovelas/senora-acero-quinta-temporada/|website=peopleenespanol.com|publisher=[[People en Espa\u00f1ol]]|accessdate=21 February 2018|language=Spanish}}</ref> On 8 November 2018, it was announced that the fifth season would be the show's final season.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gonz\u00e1lez |first1=Mois\u00e9s |title=Se\u00f1ora Acero llega a su fin |url=https://peopleenespanol.com/telenovelas/senora-acero-llega-a-su-fin/ |website=peopleenespanol.com |publisher=[[People en Espa\u00f1ol]] |accessdate=9 November 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |user=SraAcero|number=1061064260736888833|date=11 November 2018|title=La saga llega a su final. \u00bfC\u00f3mo terminar\u00e1 la historia de Los Acero? No se pierdan ni un solo cap\u00edtulo de #SraAcero5 #TemporadaFinal|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n== Series overview ==\n{{Main|List of Se\u00f1ora Acero episodes|label 1=List of ''Se\u00f1ora Acero'' episodes}}\n{{:List of Se\u00f1ora Acero episodes}}\nThe series follows the life of Sara Aguilar Berm\u00fadez ([[Blanca Soto]]), a woman who has everything anyone can want in life. She is so happy, that nothing tells her what fate has prepared for her. The day that she decides to marry for the church with her husband Vicente Acero ([[Dami\u00e1n Alc\u00e1zar]]), at the request of her son Salvador, a paramilitary command assassinates her husband. Sara changes her life forever because she discovers that her husband was not who she believed. This is how the opportunity comes to Sara to take revenge on all those who hurt her and tried to sink her as she struggled to get along with her son.\n\nIn season two, after remaining in prison for five years, Sara hopes to be released for lack of evidence. However, the president of the Republic, at the request of his private secretary, Berta Aguilar ([[Luciana Silveyra]]), has sentenced Sara to 25 years in prison. The hatred of a resentful sister, the political ambitions of a corrupt president, and another bad move of destiny, plunge Se\u00f1ora Acero into a deep depression. Once again it is her turn to say goodbye to his son Salvador ([[Michel Duval]]) and her great love, Manuel Caicedo ([[Lincoln Palomeque]]).\n\nIn season three, three years later, Vicenta ([[Carolina Miranda (actress)|Carolina Miranda]]) is one of the most respected and feared [[coyote]]s on the border between Mexico and the United States. Immigrants seek her because she has a reputation for protecting them with her life when they pass the edge. Homeland Security officials are looking for her, especially Daniel Phillips ([[Luis Ernesto Franco]]). The other coyotes want her dead because she is taking away the business. La Coyote does not know that she is a bastard daughter of narco Vicente Acero and half sister of Salvador (Michel Duval), the sole heir of the Acero Dynasty so far. Chucho Casares ([[Sergio Goyri]]) will be Vicenta's worst enemy not only because he is the murderer of her mother but because he will oppose her relationship with Abelardo, his son. For Vicenta to carry the surname Acero can be your salvation or your death sentence. What is clear is that that last name runs through her veins and that now she is the only \"Se\u00f1ora Acero\".\n\n[[Se\u00f1ora Acero (season 4)|In season four]], Vicenta Acero (Carolina Miranda), who is one of the most respected and feared [[coyote]]s on the border between Mexico and the United States; she is sought by a large number of immigrants, thanks to her reputation to protect them with their lives when they pass to the other side of the border; but because of her fame, the other coyotes want her dead, since she is taking away their business. In addition to this, Vicenta Acero is wanted by the governments of Mexico and the United States since her family is the main suspect in the death of Governor Chucho Cas\u00e1res (Sergio Goyri) and her brother Salvador (Michel Duval) is taken to jail; after leaving the hotel where he was hiding. Vicenta Acero and Daniel Phillips (Luis Ernesto Franco) are followed by the head of the [[Department of National Security]], Indira C\u00e1rdenas ([[Gaby Espino]]), and the border patrol of the state of [[Texas]]; they both are trying to prevent these two from continuing to cross immigrants at the border. Added to this, the Colombian Drug Trafficker, Juli\u00e1n Romero ([[Diego Cadavid]]) arrives in [[Mexico]] to avenge the death of his relatives and her mom, Briceida Montero. Juli\u00e1n is obsessed in finding Vicenta to carry out his purposes against Salvador and El Gallo ([[\u00d3scar Priego]]).<ref>{{cite web|title=Telemundo Upfront 2017: 13 Telenovelas & Series You Must Watch Next Season|url=http://www.latintimes.com/telemundo-upfront-2017-13-telenovelas-series-you-must-watch-next-season-417563|website=latintimes.com|accessdate=11 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[Se\u00f1ora Acero (season 5)|In season five]], Vicenta Acero (Carolina Miranda), who she\u2019s pregnant during eight months, the time comes when Vicenta decides to bury her husband Daniel Philips (Luis Ernesto Franco), who died after six months have been in [[Coma (medicine)|a coma]]. During the funeral of her husband, Vicenta communicates anonymously with Alberto Fuentes ([[David Chocarro]]) [[FBI agent]] to inform him that the murderer of her husband is at the funeral, after following the track of the call, arrives at the funeral in where is Vicenta and he realizes that it was a false alarm and begins to argue with Vicenta. During the discussion Vicenta begins to give indications of giving birth and there is only time for her to give birth. Alberto of the nothing receives the son of Vicenta and between them a very strong bond is born that unites them immediately. On the other hand [[List of Se\u00f1ora Acero characters#El Teca|El Teca]] ([[William Miller (actor, born 1978)|William Miller]]), who supposedly died at the hands of [[List of Se\u00f1ora Acero characters#Salvador Acero|Salvador Acero]] (Michel Duval) 5 years ago. El Teca returns after spending 6 years in prison in the [[United States]] just to get revenge on the Acero Family, who ended up with his entire family and his cartel. His only goal is to kill Vicenta's son. Vicenta and Salvador both dedicated to the breeding of horses and Josefina and El Gallo dedicated to politics, have been completely isolated from all the problems for 6 years and away from any danger, but suddenly they will be forced to flee when they find out about the repair of El Teca. Who will use unimaginable methods to destroy them all. Meanwhile [[List of Se\u00f1ora Acero characters#La Tuti|La Tuti]] ([[Ana Luc\u00eda Dom\u00ednguez]]) has managed to keep her son out of Mexico thanks to the profits she has obtained in her business of exotic dancers, but she will be forced to be always protected by guaruras, to avoid that El Teca extorts her and wants to take away her son \u00c1lvaro. Despite all her efforts to keep her family together and safe, Vicenta will make a difficult decision; Get away from your family and your new love together with your child. Away from her family, Vicenta together with her son will face many dangers, but not everything is bad for her, on the way away from her family and the whole world she meets Lucas Iglesias (Guillermo Zulueta), a [[hippie]] who gives her an inn on the beach where he works. In this new refuge, she meets La Mecha ([[Mar\u00eda Rojo]]), who suddenly becomes a new mother for Vicenta; and Nancy ([[Patricia Manterola]]) who becomes her best friend. In this new world in which everyone just wants to defend their children, Vicenta and La Tuti join forces to end El Teca, and thus be able to give their children a better future and to sleep in peace.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{Main|List of Se\u00f1ora Acero characters|l1=List of ''Se\u00f1ora Acero'' characters}}\n{{Div col|colwidth=25em}}\n* [[Blanca Soto]] as [[List of Se\u00f1ora Acero characters#Sara Aguilar|Sara Aguilar]] (seasons 1\u20132)\n* [[Litzy]] as [[List of Se\u00f1ora Acero characters#Aracely Paniagua|Aracely Paniagua]] (seasons 1\u20133)\n* [[Dami\u00e1n Alc\u00e1zar]] as [[List of Se\u00f1ora Acero characters#Vicente Acero|Vicente Acero]]  (season 1; [[stand-in]] season 3)<ref name=\"guest\" group=\"Note\">Despite only appearing in a few episodes in individual seasons, is credited as main.</ref><ref name=\"stand\" group=\"Note\">In season 3, Alc\u00e1zar only appears as [[archive footage]], but in some episodes another unknown actor appears playing the character.</ref>\n* [[Marco P\u00e9rez (actor)|Marco P\u00e9rez]] as  [[List of Se\u00f1ora Acero characters#Felipe Murillo|Felipe Murillo]] (season 1)\n* [[Jorge Z\u00e1rate (actor)|Jorge Z\u00e1rate]] as  [[List of Se\u00f1ora Acero characters#El Indio Amaro|El Indio Amaro]] (seasons 1\u20134)\n* [